start.label: not all it's cracked up to be

examples.en: He claimed that he'd been cheated.
The accident claimed many lives.
I never claimed to be infallible.
She claimed that I cheated at chess.
Lost property can be claimed between 10 a.m. and 4 p.m.
He claimed that he killed the burglar.
They claimed the body of the executed traitor.
Both of them claimed credit for the idea.
They claimed it was simply an oversight.
A baron claimed his barony as a proprietor.
He claimed that a witch had put a hex on him.
She claimed she'd been threatened with the sack.
The discoverer claimed the island for the nation.
He claimed that the evidence against him was a plant.
The ancient Chinese claimed that garlic promoted longevity.
The report claimed that the disaster was wholly unavoidable.
She claimed she had been subjected to abuse and foul language.
Magical properties are sometimes claimed for certain medicines.
He claimed he had been illegally detained.
No one ever claimed authorship for the poem.
He claimed compensation for loss of earnings.
They claimed on the maximum allowable amount.
He claimed to have the power of the evil eye.
He claimed he could divine underground water.
He claimed his suitcases at the airline counter.
She claimed to have been a victim of child abuse.
The group claimed responsibility for the bombings.
The earthquake has so far claimed over 3000 lives.
She claimed she had been mistreated by the police.
She claimed to be a direct descendant of Wordsworth.
